VETERAN singer, John Asiemo, aka Daddy Showkey, has shared reasons he will forever remain grateful to the Minister of Niger Delta Affairs, Godswill Akpabio. Daddy Showkey, on an Instagram live, recounted how the former two-term governor of the Akwa Ibom State and immediate past Senate Minority assisted him after he was involved in an auto crash years back in Europe.   WurlD: I’m lucky to be accepted back in Nigeria     Lere Paimo returns to screen for Adedibu’s biopic by Seun…     Yung6ix speaks on new genre, Trapfro   He said: “For the hospital wey I dey for Europe, I just dey tell myself say Daddy Showkey na like so I take die, I con tell God say if I no die that my name wey you give me no go die. Today now I know say people go dey curse Godswill Apkabio, how dey expect me to curse the man wey take care of me, who pay the hospital bill for me, you know how much I spend for the hospital? For three years why I no fit waka, you can insult him if you like but for me, I will always be grateful to him so if I go right now say make I go greet am person go con tell me say why I go greet am no, you have a right to vote for who you want to vote for or talk about who you want to talk for.” The 51-year-old singer however noted that he has chosen not to engage in politics but rather focus on his recently launched app, ‘Confam Made.’